metadata.name: PARIS-BXL #47
metadata.description:
PARIS-BXL is a generative loop and animated piece creating shapes based on trails.
The size, position and motion frequency of each trails are generated for each token, along with the color theme.
The loop is also clipped in a generated circle.

Each reloading creates a different movement, as the algorithm underlying the piece is partially based on a noise.

Created by Quentin Hocdé, in Paris (France).

metadata.name: Qubitscape #105
metadata.description:
Qubitscape is my painterly approach to a flowfields with colors and circular shape modifier. There are 12 color palettes and 10 visual output styles. 

"Animated" style has 10% probability

"Wildcard Rainbow" style is the of the styles with %5 probability and wide range of parameters

In a Qubitscape there is always a probability of anomalies by color or by pattern. Look out for them! 

For more information check out : https://www.muratatimtay.com

Created with p5js. 
Creation Date: 12/17/2021
Murat Atimtay

metadata.name: Mythic Latent Glitches  #170
metadata.description:
What is even real and what is artificial?

In the contemporary light, the division between real and artificial loses weight as the concepts become more and more intertwined. In this work, the artist combines the human and generative inputs, in a counterintuitive manner, by allowing AI to design the organic elements and using the human hand to incorporate artificial glitches. What seemingly emerges as natural forms, was imagined solely by GAN, seeing the world through the limited examples through the photographer’s lenses. Artist’s role is also reversed, as their goal is to design the visual destruction process of the organic forms. Glitch is a malfunction of perception, it symbolizes the confusion caused by not being able to comprehend. 

The human fascination with metaphysical forces spans many centuries. While Pagan mythology created gods living in deep forests and under-explored territories, nowadays we approach technology with somewhat similar awe, fascination, and fear. 

The project has been developed in multiple stages. It started with an inspiration by the Lithuanian landscape and research of the ancient myths and legends. The photography aimed at capturing the mysterious, spanning months and years of different experiences. A custom pre-trained artist’s GAN model was then trained on a collection of several hundred photographs in high resolution. Selected outputs were curated by artist and included as a starting canvas for the next stage. Then, a set of stochastic manipulations were programmed to create alternative narratives through the visual destruction. Fog turns into smoke into burning radioactive forest in an unpredictable manner, guided by the random variables, their boundaries crafted by artist.  

Read more on the project website:
ivonatau.com/mythic-latent-glitches

- Use the "A" key to animate (if "Animated" feature is present).
- Press any key to stop the animation.
- Use the "S" key to export an image.

metadata.name: intersection #1
metadata.description:
I have long meant to do a piece inspired by the covers of the famous (to the sort of people that like Dutch electronic music from the 1950s) Philips "Popular Electronics" 7" records. Yesterday I finally sat down and did one. "intersection" takes as its source material the cover art of the first record in the set, "Electronic Music," which is a split single by Tom Dissevelt and Kid Battan. You can listen to it on YouTube if you are curious. (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=z6T-jZUHcI8 and it's a banger!)

Rather than recreating the cover art directly, I just briefly looked at it (I have the real vinyl records, because I'm the sort of person that has strange things like that) to wedge it in my brain, and then didn't look at it again. As a result, my piece has the "feel" of the record cover, but doesn't actually look like it at all. This is a satisfying result for me. 

Created in p5.js.

metadata.name: Abstract Attractorism #2
metadata.description:
Painted strange attractors in charcoal, acrylic, and colored pencils.

The piece has several phases: background, charcoal sketch, painting, finishing, and then starting over building up layers.

For each seed, the first painting is consistent for all platforms. Paintings after that may slightly vary between browsers. 

Press 'p' to pause and 's' to take a screenshot at any time. The image size is 1400x1082 which is the aspect ratio of a standard printer paper.

Features
- 200 possible palettes
- 3 possible color distribution methods
- 50% colored pencil border on completion
- Distribution of brush qualities and color variance from the palette colors

20% chance of rare
- More variation in the attractor functions for more unique results
- Small brush strokes with a longer paint time

10% chance of super rare
- Everything from rare
- Guaranteed large color blocks instead of smaller chaotic random color distribution
- Tape border when it's finished

metadata.name: Cosmo Fibrils #70
metadata.description:
As a child browsing through an encyclopedia (Tout l'Univers), I stumbled upon a printed photograph of a nebulae. It felt so familiar although I couldn't have ever seen one before. I felt projected into a vibrant novel universe. To this day, this rhapsodic experience remains deeply imprinted in me. This piece is my expression for its nostalgia.

The drawing has been slowed down on purpose for the viewer to enjoy its fibrous shaping.
Please be patient and relax.

I sincerely hope you will enjoy your lucky token.

Emile Jaaa

metadata.name: (Syn)thesis #86
metadata.description:
This p5.js algorithm is a reimagining of my first collection, (Anti)thesis, with a focus this time on compositions made up of shapes, colours, and textures that were hand-selected for their cohesiveness and balance to evoke a sense of calm.

In the spirit of 2022, each token consists of 2 works, the initial one and a second, in the same palette, which appears when the canvas is clicked on. 

Pressing ‘S’ in live mode saves a hi-resolution PNG copy.
